&lt;h3&gt;Who We Are:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Airia, we&#39;re a team of innovators, technologists, and problem-solvers united by a shared vision: making enterprise AI accessible, secure and impactful. Our diverse team brings together deep expertise in artificial intelligence, enterprise software, and industry-specific knowledge to tackle the most pressing challenges facing modern businesses. We believe in responsible innovation, putting our customers&#39; needs first, and building solutions that create lasting value.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are a creative and detail-oriented Graphic Designer with a passion for visual storytelling and branding. You thrive in a fast-paced environment and are able to transform complex ideas into compelling visuals. You have excellent communication skills and are adept at collaborating with cross-functional teams to deliver high-quality design solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Graphic Designer at Airia, you will support the marketing team by creating engaging and visually appealing graphics and layouts for various marketing materials. This can be a part-time or full-time contract.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Core Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop visual concepts and designs for digital and print marketing materials, including brochures, social media graphics, tradeshow booths, email campaigns, and web graphics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with the marketing team to ensure designs align with brand guidelines and effectively communicate key messages.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and edit visual content for presentations, infographics, and other promotional materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay updated on design trends and best practices to ensure innovative and effective design solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage multiple projects simultaneously while adhering to deadlines and maintaining high-quality standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Need from You:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience as a Graphic Designer or in a similar role, with a strong portfolio showcasing your design skills and creativity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in designing enterprise, B2B marketing materials.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in design software such as Adobe Creative Suite (Photoshop, Illustrator, InDesign).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience designing Tradeshow booths and materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of typography, color theory, and layout principles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently and collaboratively within a team environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent time management skills and the ability to handle multiple projects with varying deadlines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Airia is an equal opportunity employer, and all qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, age, sex, national origin, disability status, genetics, protected veteran status, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, or any other characteristic protected by federal, state, or local laws.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

