&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Airia, LLC seeks a Staff Full Stack Engineer in Alpharetta (Atlanta), Georgia.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job duties:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate on the design and development of modern and user-friendly AI solutions and mobile applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize front-end technologies (e.g., React, Angular) to create engaging user interfaces.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop server-side logic using back-end technologies like C# or Java.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Integrate third-party APIs and services to enhance application functionality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure the security and privacy of healthcare data through effective implementation of best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct testing, debugging, and troubleshooting to identify and address software issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Customize software solutions to optimize operational solutions after analyzing user needs and software requirements to determine design feasibility.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional teams to implement continuous improvements and updates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apply knowledge of engineering principles, best practices, and technologies to the design, development, testing and production of various Airia products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Part-time telecommuting permitted within the Atlanta, GA MSA, with in-office requirement (Monday, Tuesday and Thursday).&lt;/p&gt;
